# Claude Code agentic infrastructure — tracking policy
#
# Intent: hooks are shared infrastructure and MUST be tracked so every agent
# (and every worktree created from main) inherits the same operational scripts.
# State directories hold a mix of durable artifacts (merge logs, batch state
# schemas worth reviewing) and ephemeral caches (last-flush timestamps, PR-
# status snapshots) — we track the former and ignore the latter.

# Ephemeral caches — never track
state/**/.last-flush
state/**/.last-compaction
state/**/.current-batch-id
state/**/.pr-status-cache

# Per-agent worktrees — never track (already in root .gitignore; this is belt-and-suspenders)
worktrees/

# Re-include durable state artifacts that would otherwise be caught by root
# .gitignore rules (root ignores *.log globally; we need progress.log tracked).
!state/**/*.log
!state/**/*.md
!state/**/*.json

# Everything else under .claude/ IS tracked by default — hooks/, state/*.json,
# state/*.log, state/*.md, agents/, commands/, settings.json, plans-archive/
